A renowned Kano-based Qur’anic reciter, Sheikh Ahmad Sulaiman, has been kidnapped along Sheme-Kankara road in Katsina State. The Chief Imam of Government House, Kano, Juma’at mosque, Ustaz Mujtaba Ibrahim Abubakar broke the news of the kidnapping shortly after the Juma’at congregational prayer. He said the scholar was kidnapped alongside five other clerics on their way back to Kano from Kebbi State.  Famous Kano Qur'anic reciter kidnapped Qur’anic reciters honour Shekarau, Alqadi Walking down Sheikh Ramadan’s memory lane